Qué bola, mi amor? 🌿
Cuban slang for What’s up, my love?
.
We had a very delicious preview of Kuba, opening soon next month in the Mission district of SF. The craft cocktails are expertly mixed by @mfarrell25 , don’t miss the Purple Reign (lavender and violet vodka) and Pucker Up (sour 🍒 and mezcal) drinks. 
.
Food wise, the salad with fresh quince fruit, juicy jerk chicken with coconut rice, and Cajun shrimp were winners. And ending on a sweet note with passion fruit cheesecake and caramel flan is never wrong 😋
.
This space is great for large groups or intimate get togethers (formerly the Cha Cha Cha space). Thank you @adineplanstheparty and @mfarrell25 for hosting such a special night for us!
.

I know how exciting it can be to attend a beautifully decorated and special event, but for the love of god, please use some party etiquette and common sense. This day is about celebrating two people getting married. IT ISN’T ABOUT YOU. You won’t lose your seat, as we have been planning this for at least a year, so you don’t need to put your big ass red purse on your chair. same for your navy blazer dudes. The bride and groom don’t want those in their wedding pics of the dinner set up and the photographer can’t always #photoshop that out. If you get there early please hang in your car or take a walk. Every #wedding #dayofcoordinator #photographer and #videographer will thank you. when #cocktailhour starts go get a drink like all the vendors wish they could but they can’t because they are busy making the room perfect for the #brideandgroom. Also unless you have a food allergy you won’t die if you eat the entree you picked 8 weeks ago when you RSVP’ed. Eat the entree that was already made and accounted for by the caterer and stop at @innout on the way home if you are still hungry like I do after ever wedding I work #partyetiquette #weddinginspiration #pleaseandthankyou #eventplanner #eventplanning #weddingplanning #weddingplanner
